com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface VectorEntry


  • public interface VectorEntry
    An entry for the UPA Vector that can house other Container Types only. Vector is a uniform type, where Vector.containerType() indicates the single type housed in each entry. Each entry has an associated action which informs the user of how to apply the data contained in the entry
    See Also:
    VectorEntryActions, VectorEntryFlags, Vector

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears VectorEntry object. Useful for object reuse during encoding. While decoding, VectorEntry object can be reused without using clear().

      • encode

        int encode(EncodeIterator iter)
        Encodes single vector item, "moving" to the next row if necessary. Must be called after encodeSetDefsComplete() and/or encodeSummaryDataComplete(). Typical use:
        1. Call Vector.encodeInit()
        2. Call VectorEntry.encode() for each entry using the same buffer
        3. Call Vector.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeInit

        int encodeInit(EncodeIterator iter,
               int maxEncodingSize)
        Prepare a single vector item for encoding. Must be called after encodeSetDefsComplete() and/or encodeSummaryDataComplete(). Typical use:
        1. Call Vector.encodeInit()
        2. Call VectorEntry.encodeInit()..VectorEntry.encodeComplete() for each entry using the same buffer
        3. Call Vector.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator
        maxEncodingSize - max encoding size of the data
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeComplete

        int encodeComplete(EncodeIterator iter,
                   boolean success)
        Completes a vector element encoding. Typical use:
        1. Call Vector.encodeInit()
        2. Call VectorEntry.encodeInit()..VectorEntry.encodeComplete() for each entry using the same buffer
        3. Call Vector.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        success - If true - successfully complete the aggregate, if false - remove the aggregate from the buffer.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator
